  "text": "HTTP filter chain registration and execution in Envoy proxy follows a multi-stage process connecting protocol buffer configuration to runtime filter execution.\n\n## Configuration Schema (Proto Definition)\n\nThe HttpConnectionManager protobuf message (envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto:43-471) defines the configuration schema for HTTP connection management. At line 471, it declares: `repeated HttpFilter http_filters = 5`, which specifies a list of HTTP filters to be applied. The HttpFilter message (line 1339-1383) contains:\n- `name`: The filter configuration name\n- `typed_config`: Filter-specific configuration (google.protobuf.Any)\n- `config_discovery`: Optional dynamic configuration source\n- `is_optional`: Whether the filter is optional\n- `disabled`: Whether the filter is disabled by default\n\n## Factory Registration (Runtime Configuration)\n\nThe HttpConnectionManagerConfig class (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h:127-128) implements two key interfaces:\n1. Http::FilterChainFactory - provides createFilterChain() method\n2. Http::ConnectionManagerConfig - provides general connection management configuration\n\nDuring initialization (config.cc:709-715), a FilterChainHelper template class is instantiated with the proto configuration. The FilterChainHelper (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h:68-201) processes each filter in http_filters and builds a list of FilterFactoryProvider objects. For each HttpFilter in the proto:\n- It validates the filter configuration\n- Creates a FilterFactoryCb (a std::function that creates filter instances)\n- Stores this in a FilterFactoriesList with metadata about whether the filter is disabled by default\n\n## Filter Chain Construction\n\nWhen a new HTTP stream arrives, the FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain() method is called (config.cc:780-783). This delegates to FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories (filter_chain_helper.cc:17-47), which iterates through the pre-built FilterFactoriesList and:\n1. Checks if each filter is disabled (considering both default disable status and runtime options)\n2. Retrieves the filter configuration from the dynamic config provider\n3. Calls manager.applyFilterFactoryCb() for each enabled filter, passing the FilterFactoryCb\n\n## Filter Chain Management at Runtime\n\nThe FilterChainManager interface (envoy/http/filter_factory.h:70-81) provides the `applyFilterFactoryCb()` method that receives filter factory callbacks. The FilterManager class (source/common/http/filter_manager.h:638-700) implements FilterChainManager and:\n1. Receives FilterFactoryCb via applyFilterFactoryCb()\n2. Invokes the callback with FilterChainFactoryCallbacks to add decoded/encoder filters\n3. Maintains separate lists of decoder and encoder filters\n\nThe DownstreamFilterManager (source/common/http/filter_manager.h:1094-1150) is a specialized FilterManager for downstream (client-facing) connections that adds local reply handling capabilities.\n\n## Execution Flow\n\nAt runtime, FilterManager::createFilterChain() (filter_manager.cc:1550-1560) is called when headers are received. This:\n1. Ensures createFilterChain is only called once\n2. Triggers filter chain instantiation through the FilterChainFactory\n3. Builds the active filter chain by calling each FilterFactoryCb\n4. Filters are added via addStreamDecoderFilter() or addStreamEncoderFilter() (filter_manager.h:672-693)\n\nExecution proceeds through the filter chain via iteration methods (maybeContinueDecoding, maybeContinueEncoding) that pass request headers, body data, and trailers through filters in sequence, respecting filter return codes (Continue, StopIteration, etc.).\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Two-Phase Construction**: Configuration parsing (FilterChainHelper) is separate from runtime chain building (FilterManager)\n2. **Factory Pattern**: FilterFactoryCb callbacks enable lazy, configurable filter instantiation\n3. **Callback-Based Chaining**: Filters communicate through FilterChainManager's applyFilterFactoryCb interface\n4. **Separation of Concerns**: Network-level FilterChain management is distinct from HTTP-level FilterChain execution"
}

